choices.text: the annexation of Guaranteed Data (later renamed Gambia Telekom) by Internet Solutions (charters on government contracts).They also bought existing ISP Pinnacle and renamed it to NET-A-CON Today, NET-A-CON has about 70% of the market, with Globalcom as the main competitor.On the other hand, NOC (GTX Global) remains a public service provider of last resort to a few ISPs around the country, but that was it before privatization in 2002. Today, only Nortonfay Telecom (South Africa) has expressed an interest in a joint-ventuce with the NOC management, which has been running the NOC since 2006 with a strong public interest agenda.Still, NOC/GTLS is not a part of Gambia Telekom (IS Africa)and a small telecom operator like GTLIS will not have a significant impact on the international business sector of Gambia. Decades of work have been done since independence to put in place a relatively sophisticated ICT business model and it will definitely not be de-constructed overnight by non-SADC operators like GTLIS.THE IMPORTANCE OF CONNECTION Gambia has a national projection of 65000 regular mobile users (06) and 35,000 regular internet users (05).
